---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Jazz — Music Terms That Score Big"
  description="Jazz music words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SWING 9pts, RIFF 10pts, SCAT 6pts, BEBOP 11pts. Jazz vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble jazz words, music scrabble terms, swing scrabble points, riff scrabble, scat scrabble word, bebop scrabble, jazz terms scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Jazz — Music Terms That Score Big","description":"Jazz music words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SWING 9pts, RIFF 10pts, SCAT 6pts, BEBOP 11pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-jazz"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is RIFF a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! RIFF scores 10 points (R=1, I=1, F=4, F=4). It's a repeated musical phrase in jazz. The double F tiles (4pts each) deliver 8 of the 10 points from just 4 letters — excellent efficiency."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is SWING worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SWING scores 9 points (S=1, W=4, I=1, N=1, G=2). It's a style of jazz music characterised by a strong rhythm section. The W tile (4pts) and G tile (2pts) make up most of the score."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is SCAT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SCAT scores 6 points (S=1, C=3, A=1, T=1) and means vocal improvisation using nonsense syllables. The C tile (3pts) provides the scoring power in this short 4-letter word."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Jazz — Music Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Jazz vocabulary hits all the right notes on a Scrabble board. Short punchy words like RIFF and SCAT combine with longer terms like SWING and BEBOP for a versatile scoring repertoire. These words use F, W, and B tiles effectively — consonants that often languish on your rack.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BEBOP (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RIFF</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SWING</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SCAT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Jazz Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">BEBOP — 11 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">B=3, E=1, B=3, O=1, P=3 · 5 letters · Triple-B/P combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A style of jazz developed in the 1940s featuring complex harmonies and rapid tempos. BEBOP uses three 3-point consonants (B, B, P) with two 1-point vowels. At 11 points from 5 tiles (2.2 per tile), it's one of the best ways to dump a double-B rack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎵 RIFF</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · R=1, I=1, F=4, F=4 · Repeated musical phrase</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎷 SWING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · S=1, W=4, I=1, N=1, G=2 · Rhythmic jazz style</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎤 SCAT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 pts · S=1, C=3, A=1, T=1 · Vocal improvisation</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎺 VAMP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · V=4, A=1, M=3, P=3 · Repeating accompaniment</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Jazz Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TEMPO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHORD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GROOVE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MODAL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LICK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BLUES</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Jazz Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">RIFF dumps double-F racks:</span> Drawing two F tiles (4pts each) is tough to play — RIFF solves it instantly. 10 points from 4 tiles, no rare letters needed beyond the Fs you already hold.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SWING uses W productively:</span> W (4pts) often sits alone on your rack. SWING pairs it with S, I, N, G — all common tiles — for a reliable 9-point play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BEBOP is the double-B solution:</span> Two Bs on your rack is awkward. BEBOP clears both while adding P for 11 total points. Remember this word whenever you see B-B.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Jazz words specialise in <span class="text-white font-medium">using duplicate tiles</span> — double F (RIFF), double B (BEBOP), and awkward consonants like W (SWING) and V (VAMP). When your rack looks unplayable, think jazz.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-circus-acts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Circus Acts</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-celtic/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Celtic Mythology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-fencing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Fencing</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid jazz word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
